http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: A one year technology based course designed as an alternative for the traditional Workplace/Career Readiness course. The course creates a link with EAST technology and methodology and focuses on teaching students the transferable skills they need to succeed in the changing workplace.
Career Awareness
Identify or confirm an interest in a particular field
Explore the Internet and other resources for career information and document findings
Interview community members about careers of interest and document findings

Participate in real-life activity related to the student's career interest area (i.e. job shadow, mentoring program, part-time employment, internship, entrepreneurship/self-employment situations are acceptable
Assess your skills, abilities, interests, experience, and accomplishments
Give examples of how math, English, science, art, music and/or foreign language are used in the chosen career area
Analyze and appraise how academic skills are used in the chosen career area
Describe how self-direction is important to the career decision making process
Analyze steps employed to determine career choice
Outline a multi-media presentation describing the reasons for making a particular career choice
Using lab equipment, produce a presentation describing the results of career investigation
Present a speech on a career/technology related topic
Identify entrepreneurial opportunities related to personal career interests
Summarize the obligations of an entrepreneur
Compare the risks and advantages of ownership
Give examples of franchise businesses
